sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as Platform Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant KRBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant VLLM as vLLM Server (vllm-gaudi)<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant HPU as Intel Gaudi HPU<br/>Synapse AI 1.23.0
    participant Storage as Model Storage<br/>(PVC / S3)

    Note over Client,Storage: Flow 1: Model Inference Request

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer Token<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+
    Gateway->>KRBAC: Forward request<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS 1.2+
    KRBAC->>KRBAC: SubjectAccessReview<br/>(validate Bearer Token)
    KRBAC->>VLLM: Proxy request<br/>HTTP/8000 (localhost, plaintext)
    VLLM->>VLLM: Tokenize input<br/>(HF Transformers)
    VLLM->>HPU: Schedule inference<br/>(Synapse AI device API)
    Note over HPU: Graph compilation<br/>or cache hit<br/>(bucketing system)
    HPU-->>VLLM: Generated tokens
    VLLM-->>KRBAC: JSON Response
    KRBAC-->>Gateway: HTTPS Response
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON Response<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+

    Note over Client,Storage: Flow 1a: Model Loading (first request / cold start)

    VLLM->>Storage: Load model weights<br/>HTTP/HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: AWS IAM / ServiceAccount
    Storage-->>VLLM: Model artifacts<br/>(weights, tokenizer, config)
    VLLM->>HPU: Transfer weights to HPU memory
    VLLM->>HPU: Warmup: compile graphs<br/>for bucket sizes

    participant Ray as Ray Head (rank 0)
    participant Worker as Ray Workers (rank 1-N)
    participant HCCL as HCCL<br/>(libfabric/verbs)

    Note over Ray,HCCL: Flow 2: Distributed Multi-Card Inference (Tensor Parallelism)

    Ray->>Worker: Distribute inference task<br/>Ray internal / gRPC<br/>(intra-pod, no encryption)
    Worker->>HPU: Execute partial forward pass<br/>(Synapse AI device API)
    HPU->>HCCL: all-reduce / all-gather<br/>Ephemeral ports<br/>HCCL protocol (no encryption)
    HCCL-->>HPU: Synchronized tensors
    HPU-->>Worker: Partial results
    Worker-->>Ray: Aggregated output
